&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for a Project Manager to work 2 days a week on a 1 year contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To play a pivotal role in the delivery of high quality primary health care within the Primary Care Network (PCN).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the PCN Clinical Director and the constituent practices to ensure the smooth running of the PCN.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be involved in the management and development of the PCN.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be responsible for the production of performance and quality reports within the PCN and other Network initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To be responsible for the oversight of the PCNs financial systems/payments to all the practices within the PCN.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the PCN is compliant with the GDPR and FOI along with other relevant legislation and professional information management standards such as GMC/BMA and LMC guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is also being advertised on the Essex Primary Care Careers website – please complete only one application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have the right to close the advert earlier if we reach the maximum number of applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NO AGENCIES PLEASE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;  Please see the attached job spec for full details of the role.   About Us:   Rickmansworth and Chorleywood PCN comprises of 3 practices, The Colne Practice, Gade Surgery and  Chorleywood Health Centre with a combines patient population of approximately 29,000 patients.   &lt;/p&gt;
